data.description: The meticulously maintained residence in the charming Suncoast Lakes community offers an array of enticing features. With 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and a den, this home is ideal for families or those seeking extra space. The 2-car attached garage includes convenient built-in storage shelves. Step outside to discover an oversized extended lanai, complete with a 5-person hot tub and a fenced backyard. One of the property's standout features is the impressive 15-foot stackable sliding glass doors that seamlessly connect the family room to the lanai, creating the perfect space for entertaining. The interior is bathed in natural light, thanks to the soaring 11.4-foot ceilings in the family room, living room, and dining room.    The kitchen is a chef's dream, equipped with granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, and a pantry closet. The master bedroom, with its 9.4-foot ceilings, provides ample room for a king-size bed and a cozy sitting area. It also offers direct access to the lanai. The master bathroom boasts double vanity sinks, a relaxing soaking tub, and a separate tiled shower. Additional living spaces include a formal living room and dining room, along with a den. Tile floors grace the main living areas, and the AC was completed in 2019. The bow on top of this present is the fact that the roof is also just one year old.    The Suncoast Lakes community provides a range of amenities, including a community pool, tennis courts, basketball courts, a playground, and picnic areas. Conveniently located near the Suncoast Trails and Suncoast Parkway, this property offers an easy commute to Tampa Airport, shopping centers, and restaurants, making it the perfect place to call home.
